Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_hire.model.manager

Class Position

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_hire.model.manager.Position
public class Position extends Object
The Position Class represents one specific position. It maintains its name, and the list of applications for the one specific position.
Author:
John Eakes

  • Constructor Details

    • Position

      public Position(String positionName, int hoursPerWeek, int payRate)
      This is the constructor for the Position Class. It takes in the three position variables and assigns them values.
      Parameters:
      positionName - the name of a specific position
      hoursPerWeek - the number of hours of a specific position
      payRate - the rate of pay of a specific position
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if positionName is null or empty, hours are less than 5 or more than 20, or payRate is less than 7 or greater than 35
